Generics is used for type safety, We can apply generics in Class, Interface, Methods and constuctor.
For example We have one list and we are trying to add values..
Before java 1.5
List list = new ArrayList();
list.add(10);
list.add("amit");

While adding data it allows to add any data but while fetching the data JVM forces type cast the values it can be integer string or
any other EX.(It can be in runtime).

Integer i = (Integer)list.get(0); 
String str = (String)list.get(1); 


In java 1.5 generics intoduced to resolve that issue.

List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(1);
list.add("str"); It will give compile time error..


